 alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/B3YUMfb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MQVdefi.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XVLszgJ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Jonson71]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Dale, What are you going to wear</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/J8RPVvB</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/62rw498.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This man was a teacher for 40 years.

In 1974, Dale Irby, a gym teacher in Dallas, realized he had worn the same outfit as the previous year on Picture Day, and decided to simply go with it, after Cathy – his wife – dared him to.

